data.description: Exceptional 43.7± acre property includes three homes, vineyard, and breathtaking views of the Sierra Nevada mountains.  Mariposa, known for its rich history and proximity to Yosemite National Park, adds a distinct charm to the location.  The main home offers approximately 3,000± square feet of living space, complemented by a vast 2,400± square-foot porch area (including a covered space of 1,270± square feet).  With 3 bedrooms, 2.5 baths, a living room, dining room, kitchen, pantry, wet bar, family room, laundry room, sunroom, and garage, the Main Home is a haven of comfort and convenience. Notable features include 10-foot ceilings, a fireplace, Viking range, and radiant heating. Antique light fixtures and fans, along with tasteful crown molding, add a touch of elegance.  Steeped in history, the charming historic cottage, dating back to 1893, covers 850± square feet and serves as a popular vacation rental.  It includes a welcoming living room, a functional dining room, a well-appointed kitchen, a bathroom, and 3 cozy bedrooms. A wood stove adds rustic charm, while wraparound porches on three sides offer ample space for outdoor relaxation.  The Caretaker cabin, spanning 994± square feet, presents comfortable living with a living room, a newly updated kitchen with an attached eating area, 2 bedrooms, bathroom, a wood stove, and attractive hardwood floors.  A 7±  acre vineyard, established in the 1990s, graces the property with Cabernet Sauvignon and Sangiovese varietals, known for producing gold medal wines. The estate's water needs are met by two wells and a substantial 7,000-gallon storage tank.   Additional storage is provided by several outbuildings.  In essence, this property combines natural beauty, luxurious living, and a touch of history set against the stunning backdrop of the Sierra Nevada mountains and proximity to the iconic Yosemite National Park.
